The paper deals with the task of version identification in music, which involves detecting recordings of the same underlying musical piece. This task involves techniques from information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (ML), which are both sub-categories of computer science. The paper also focuses on the use of embeddings, which are commonly used in machine learning for dimensionality reduction and similarity comparisons. This makes the paper relevant to sub-categories such as cs.SD (Sound), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Among these, cs.SD and cs.IR are the most likely categories, as they directly relate to the task of version identification and the techniques used in the paper.
